<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-09-0241 </DOCNO><TEXT>The two authors debate the issue of a U.S. Defense policy. Both agreethat there should be a strong cohesion of policies, strategies, and capabilities,which is now lacking. They agree that the United States cannot with confidencemeet current commitments and officially established defense requirementswith present programs and levels of spending. However, one author sayswe are overcommitted and overspending on defense. The other author saysour national security and global interests are being threatened by failureto do enough, not by spending too much on defense. Arguments by bothauthors are presented.</TEXT></DOC>